10/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The EU High Representative in Skopje, Soren Jessen-Petersen, expects to see a fair and comprehensive campaign in the upcoming emergency presidential election, said EU spokeswoman Sheena Thompson.
Speaking Tuesday (9 March), she said unity among political parties is crucial to Macedonia's planned EU membership application.
Also Tuesday, police in Skopje arrested a former member of the rebel National Liberation Army, Izair Samiu, also known as Commander Baci.
He was sentenced to two years in prison for possession of illegal weapons in 2002, but had been in hiding ever since.
(Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 10/03/04;
Makfax - 09/03/04)
